text: You all are the living, breathing proof that the American Dream endures in our time. ‚ÄîThe First Lady to the @CityCollegeNY Class of 2016
Public education is our greatest pathway to opportunity in America, so we need to invest in and strengthen our public universities ‚ÄîFLOTUS
It means reaching back to help young people who've been left out and left behind, helping them prepare for college ‚ÄîFLOTUS #ReachHigher
That means raising your hand at that board meeting and asking: 'Whose voices aren't being heard? What ideas are we missing?' ‚ÄîFLOTUS
Nothing is going to stop you from fulfilling your dreams, and you deserve every last one of the successes that I know you will have.
You should never ever be embarrassed by those struggles. You should never view your challenges as a disadvantage ‚ÄîFLOTUS at @CityCollegeNY
Neither of my parents went past high school. "They saved up every penny that my dad earned." "They were determined to send me to college."
Our greatness has always come from people who expect nothing and take nothing for granted. ‚ÄîThe First Lady at @CityCollegeNY #ReachHigher
In America, we don't let our differences tear us apart. Because we know that our greatness comes when we appreciate each other's strengths
That is the power of our differences to make us smarter, and more creative. ‚ÄîThe First Lady at @CityCollegeNY #ReachHigher
Talent and effort‚Äîcombined with our various backgrounds and life experiences‚Äîhas always been the lifeblood of our singular American genius
For centuries, this city has been the gateway to America for so many striving, hope-filled immigrants ‚ÄîThe First Lady at @CityCollegeNY
No matter where your journey started, you have all made it here today through...unyielding determination, sacrifice, and hard work ‚ÄîFLOTUS
At this school, you represent more than 150 nationalities. You speak more than 100 different languages ‚ÄîThe First Lady at @CityCollegeNY
This is my last chance to share my love, admiration, & hopefully a little bit of wisdom with a graduating class ‚ÄîFLOTUS at @CityCollegeNY
I want to recognize all of you‚Äîthe brilliant, talented, ambitious, accomplished, all-around outstanding members of the Class of 2016!
It is beyond an honor and a pleasure to be here today to celebrate the City College of New York Class of 2016! ‚ÄîFLOTUS as @CityCollegeNY

text: I can't wait to see everything you will achieve and bring back to your communities. ‚ÄîThe First Lady to the @SFIS_Braves Class of 2016
I hope you will always remember your story and that you will carry your story with you as proudly as I carry mine. ‚ÄîFLOTUS to @SFIS_Braves
I try my best to pass down to my girls that same love and that same dreaming spirit that Marian and Fraser Robinson passed down to me.
Your big, impossible dreams are actually just the right size. And you have everything you need to achieve them. ‚ÄîFLOTUS to @SFIS_Braves
Graduates, today all of that lives inside of you, all of that history, all of that sacrifice, all of that love. ‚ÄîFLOTUS to @SFIS_Braves
Your communities have seeds that your ancestors have been planting and harvesting for 1000s of years, long before America was even an idea
Because by facing adversity head on and getting through it, you have gained wisdom and maturity beyond your years. ‚ÄîFLOTUS to @SFIS_Braves
Those struggles should never be a source of shame. "Those struggles are the source of your greatest strengths." ‚ÄîFLOTUS to @SFIS_Braves
You have already faced‚Äîand overcome‚Äîchallenges in your lives that most young people can‚Äôt even begin to imagine ‚ÄîFLOTUS to @SFIS_Braves
More than ever before, our world needs you too. ‚ÄîThe First Lady to the @SFIS_Braves Class of 2016
Because your communities need you, they need you to develop your potential and become who you are meant to be. ‚ÄîFLOTUS to the @SFIS_Braves
RT @ReachHigher: "I want you to reach out and ask for help...No one gets through college alone. No one. I certainly didn't" @FLOTUS https:/‚Ä¶
The minute you feel like you‚Äôre struggling, the minute, I want you to ask for help. ‚ÄîThe First Lady to @SFIS_Braves on going to college
Hold fast to your goals "Push through any obstacles that may come your way" ‚ÄîThe First Lady to the @SFIS_Braves Class of 2016 #ReachHigher
As you begin the next phase of your journey, please remember that your communities need even more of your energy and expertise. ‚ÄîFLOTUS
Every day at this school, you‚Äôve been weaving together thousands of years of your heritage with the realities of your modern lives ‚ÄîFLOTUS
Nearly all of you are going on to college. ‚ÄîThe First Lady to the @SFIS_Braves Class of 2016 #ReachHigher
Today, the Native languages that were once strictly forbidden here now echo through the hallways. ‚ÄîThe First Lady to the @SFIS_Braves
This school was founded as part of a deliberate, systematic effort to extinguish your cultures ‚ÄîThe First Lady to the @SFIS_Braves
Your stories, your achievements, your contributions, and the story of this school inspire me. ‚ÄîThe First Lady to the @SFIS_Braves
I learned integrity from my parents, that living a good life is not about being wealthy or powerful. It‚Äôs about being honest. ‚ÄîFLOTUS
Your values, the values that infuse this school, are the very same values that my parents handed down to me. ‚ÄîFLOTUS to @SFIS_Braves
There is nowhere I would rather be than right here with all of you. ‚ÄîThe First Lady to the @SFIS_Braves #ReachHigher #GenI
I will never forget the look of pride on his face, and on my mom‚Äôs face, as I walked across the stage at @Princeton & @HarvardLaw ‚ÄîFLOTUS
My parents were products of segregated schools & neither of them had an education past high school‚Ä¶they wanted their kids to go to college
I am the granddaughter of Fraser Robinson Jr., who left the only life he‚Äôd ever known to move his family north. ‚ÄîThe First Lady
I am the great-granddaughter of Fraser Robinson, an illiterate houseboy who taught himself to read and became an entrepreneur. ‚ÄîFLOTUS
I am the great-great-granddaughter of Jim Robinson, who was born in South Carolina and lived as a slave. ‚ÄîThe First Lady telling her story
I want to tell you about the people who came before me and how they made me who I am today. ‚ÄîThe First Lady
You did it. You're here. You made it. And we are all so very, very proud of you! ‚ÄîFLOTUS to the @SFIS_Braves Class of 2016 #ReachHigher

text: I urge you to raise your voices...build a better world for young women all across the globe. ‚ÄîThe First Lady https://t.co/BNUunVkFtT
Every single one of you can be a leader in this movement to empower each other. ‚ÄîThe First Lady to students in Argentina #LetGirlsLearn
#62milliongirls across the globe are not in school... imagine for a minute what it's like to be one of those girls. ‚ÄîThe First Lady
I want to urge you to get the education you need to make your voice heard in the world. ‚ÄîThe First Lady in Argentina #LetGirlsLearn
Because of my education, I had opportunities that my parents never could have dreamed of for themselves. ‚ÄîThe First Lady #LetGirlsLearn
I decided not to listen to the voices of those who doubted me. Instead, I decided to listen to my own voice ‚ÄîThe First Lady #LetGirlsLearn
I would lie awake at night with those doubts eating away at my heart. ‚ÄîThe First Lady on pursuing her goals as a young girl #LetGirlsLearn
I started to question myself... Was I too loud - or too much?  Was I too bossy? Was I dreaming too big? ‚ÄîThe First Lady #LetGirlsLearn
Messages that said as a girl, my voice was somehow less important. ‚ÄîThe First Lady on those who didn't support her dreams. #LetGirlsLearn
The hopes I had for myself were in conflict with the messages I was receiving from people around me. ‚ÄîThe First Lady #LetGirlsLearn
People who thought a girl shouldn't have ambition. ‚ÄîThe First Lady sharing the obstacles she faced growing up. #LetGirlsLearn
Teachers who didn't think I was smart enough and would call on the boys in class over the girls. ‚ÄîThe First Lady  #LetGirlsLearn
